cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.PL, cs.MA, cs.RO 

This paper deals with the integration of commonsense reasoning and probabilistic planning, which are core topics in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also introduces a new probabilistic action language (cs.PL) and applies it to the design of a system (cs.MA) that compiles a pBC+ action description into a POMDP model. Finally, the paper's focus on decision-making and planning suggests that it could also be relevant to the robotics community (cs.RO).
